ncient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Giuditta di Buonalbergo was born in 1097, in Roccasecca, Frosinone, Lazio, Italy. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Conte Roberto di Medania. She died about 1160, in her hometown, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1097–circa 1160":"1097–umbes 1160","1098–1160":"1098–1160","1124–Male":"1124–Surnud","1125–1157":"1125–1157","1097–1160":"1097–1160","1125":"1125","1125?":"1125","1157":"1157","1124":"1124","circa 1160":"umbes 1160","1098":"1098","1097":"1097","about 1124":"umbes 1124","1160":"1160","Roccasecca, Frosinone, Lazio, Italia":"Roccasecca, Frosinone, Lazio, Itaalia","Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Italia":"Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Itaalia","Europe":"Europe","Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roma, Lazio, Itaalia","Roccasecca, Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roccasecca, Roma, Lazio, Itaalia"},"fi":{"1097–circa 1160":"1097–noin 1160","1098–1160":"1098–1160","1124–Male":"1124–Kuollut","1125–1157":"1125–1157","1097–1160":"1097–1160","1125":"1125","1125?":"1125","1157":"1157","1124":"1124","circa 1160":"noin 1160","1098":"1098","1097":"1097","about 1124":"noin 1124","1160":"1160","Roccasecca, Frosinone, Lazio, Italia":"Roccasecca, Frosinone, Lazio, Italia","Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Italia":"Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Italia","Europe":"Europe","Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roma, Lazio, Italia","Roccasecca, Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roccasecca, R